Masinissa] fought for Carthage in Spain, but after a great victory of Scipio's made overtures to him. On his return to Africa he was attacked by his old neighbour and rival Syphax and the Carthaginians, but Scipio's invasion of the country saved him. He commanded the right wing at Zama.
